Most patients have been infected during sexual intercourse, which is a new development.
Historically, the virus has spread rapidly in some parts of the country as a result of contaminated blood transfusions.
However, the number of people infected with HIV in this way has been reduced to almost zero, said the Chinese health authorities at a conference in Yunnan province.
However, from year to year, the number of people living with HIV/AIDS in China has increased by 100,000.
In China's LGBT community, the transmission of HIV through sexual intercourse is a serious problem.
Homosexuality was decriminalized in China in 1997, but discrimination against the LGBT community remains widespread.
Because of the country's conservative values, studies estimate that 70 to 90 per cent of homosexual men end up marrying a woman.
